{"key":"processedPost-9501774","value":{"id":9501774,"first":9496362,"last":9501784,"when":1230402644,"utime":"12/27/08 08:30 PM","content":"DON'T use the salt method for growing mushrooms, as said repeatedly above.<br /><br />A mechanical hygrometer has a human hair attached to a spring, which is attached to the dial.&nbsp; As the humidity changes, the human hair stretches and compacts, which shows the humidity.<br /><br />Such a method is only accurate through a narrow humidity range.&nbsp; If you want it to be accurate to read ambient humidity in your house, use the salt method.&nbsp; If you want it to be accurate in your fruiting chamber, use the damp towel method.<br />RR","title":"Re: humidistat","forum":"Mushroom Cultivation"}}